descript.abstract: This GIS layer consists of the 64 Louisiana parishes (66 polygons as two parishes are divided). This state/parish boundary feature layer was generated in the Louisiana Department of Natural Resources in the early 1990s manually digitized from hard copy 1:100,000 USGS maps. At least two other state/parish boundary feature layers are in use in Louisiana: the Louisiana Department of Transportation and Development version reformatted by the LSU Louisiana Geological survey (manually digitized and updated with legal boundary changes) and the USGS National Wetlands Center version digitized from 1:24,000 USGS quadrangle map Digital Raster Graphics. The DNR version has the offshore parish boundaries and official Louisiana shoreline and the official Louisiana three mile limit of territorial waters added from CADD DXF files obtained from the Louisiana State Land Office. The other two do not.
descript.purpose: This GIS layer was created as a locational reference.

idinfo.useconst: There is no totally accurate state/parish boundary digital data set available for Louisiana. This version is a general representation of the state/parish boundaries. For detailed high resolution parish boundary location determinations, other sources should be used.
